            "description": "\"Art in Action - How can art have a positive impact on social issues?\" was a Youth Exchange held in Guimar\u00e3es, Portugal in the Autumn of 2015. The activities took place on October 9-15 (without travel days) official ending on the 15 of October, with a final presentation of the participants' works. It involved 6 countries with 5 participants each, Portugal, Netherlands, Italy, Estonia, Slovenia and Turkey. The aim of this project was to help artists to combine their work and support the community they live in. Furthermore, explore how art and design can create a positive impact on social issues. \n\nMy role in this project was as project writer, coordinator and working in the implementation of the project together with the staff from Desincoop. This includes writing the project application/request for EU funding, managing activities and project implementation as well as writing the final report. Moreover, I was responsible for all the design of promotion materials, activities and outputs of the project.",
