        {
            "title": "Be Active Be Inclusive  || Project Writer and Coordinator",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 4,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2013
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 4,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2013
                }
            },
            "description": "\u201cBe Active, Be Inclusive\u201d was a Youth Exchange project promoted by Desincoop with the funding of the European Union. It took place in Guimar\u00e3es (Portugal) European City of Sport 2013 in 22- 29 April. The main goal of this project was the promotion of inclusive communication and relations between young European citizens through sports. This project was mainly for young people between 18-25 years, with minor disabilities, problems of inclusion and young people who were interested in the subject. We had 4 participants and one leader of each country (Portugal, Czech Republic, Romania, Poland, Estonia, Turkey and Italy) during a six-day youth exchange, also supported by members of Desincoop staff.\nThe programme of activities had an interactive approach, based on the experience of the participants,\nsharing different realities and difficulties and the active participation in a common subject.\n\nMy role in this project was as project coordinator taking care of writing the funding application to the EU (in collaboration with Ana Felix), implementation of the project (in collaboration with Desincoop staff) and design of all the materials including final e-book.",
