                    "year": 2014
                }
            },
            "description": "No Borderland was a project funded by the European Union and hosted by Platform Spartak , in Den Haag 2-10 May. There was 25 participants coming from Italy, Portugal, Czech Republic,Turkey, and the Netherlands. The aim of the project was to explore the concept and meaning of \"Home\"  in a period that young people use mobility around countries in order to find better life perspectives in education, work... The approach to discuss this subject used creative and artistic methods and non formal education. The activities finished on 9th of May, day of Europe, with an exhibition of all the artworks created during the activities. \n\nMy role in this project was as project coordinator taking care of writing the funding application to the EU, final report and implementation of the project as well as design of all the materials including final e-book.",
